# S107 — Method should not have too many parameters (strict)

**Specification:** [RSPEC-107](https://rules.sonarsource.com/csharp/RSPEC-107)  
**Rule key (analyzer):** `csharpsquid:S107`

## Enforcement

This project **strictly** follows S107. Do not introduce or leave methods (including local functions and `delegate` signatures) with **more than seven parameters**.

- When adding or changing C# code, **verify** parameter count before finishing.
- If a legitimate design needs more inputs, **refactor first** using the patterns below — do not increase the Sonar threshold as a workaround.

## Compliant refactors

| Approach | Use when |
|----------|----------|
| **`record` / class / DTO** with `required` + optional init props | Factory methods, handlers, domain `Create`/`Register`/`Record` APIs |
| **Options object** or **builder** | Many optional or configuration values |
| **Split method** | Unrelated responsibilities bundled in one method |

**Avoid:** positional `record` primary constructors with 8+ parameters — they violate S107 the same as ordinary methods.

## Reviews

Treat S107 like a build breaker: the same remediation applies when reviewing PRs and when the AI suggests code.
